        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40679",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=keilnoth",
                        "name": "keilnoth",
                        "displayName": "Eric Jeker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This problem is still open in version 1.10.4.\r\n\r\nReproducing it is quite simple, just create a Zend_Form_Element_Select field with a translator enabled and no translation done and add a few values in it.\r\n\r\nAt line 311 in Zend_Form_Element_Multi, you'll see that this code is called :\r\n\r\n{code:php} \r\nif ($translator->isTranslated($value)) {\r\n    return $translator->translate($value);\r\n}\r\n{code} \r\n\r\nand Zend_Translate_Adapter->isTranslated() method doesn't log anything before returning false.\r\n\r\nSo all the values in that select field won't figure in the missing translations log.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=keilnoth",
                        "name": "keilnoth",
                        "displayName": "Eric Jeker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-25T07:38:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-25T07:38:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40685",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you please clearify if it's now a failure or not a failure.\r\nBoth states are not possible at the same time.\r\n\r\nYou should also note that logging of untranslated messages depend on the used settings for Zend_Translate. Per default log is NOT enabled because you must attach a log where Zend_Translate can write to.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-25T13:53:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-25T13:53:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40688",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=keilnoth",
                        "name": "keilnoth",
                        "displayName": "Eric Jeker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Logging of untranslated messages is activated in my test case.\r\n\r\nMy opinion is that it's a failure because it works for every other Zend components, examples: input's labels, standard translation, etc... But not in a few cases listed above or in the cloned issue.\r\n\r\nI am not talking about optimization or if we should use the isTranslated method. But only about the final result: no log entries for untranslated messages when there should be some.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=keilnoth",
                        "name": "keilnoth",
                        "displayName": "Eric Jeker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-25T14:12:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-25T14:12:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40691",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As you said that it's working I will detach Zend_Translate from the components being buggy.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-25T22:38:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-25T22:40:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40692",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "As you said there's a bug I am detaching the \"fixed for version 1.8\" tag",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-25T22:40:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-25T22:40:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40787",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Agreed and fixed for Zend_Form_Element and Zend_Dojo_Form_Element with r22322.\r\n\r\nNot agreed and no bug for Zend_Validate. Zend_Validate must provide the capability to translate the message constants as also the content.\r\n\r\nNot agreed for Zend_Translate. IsTranslated must not throw a notice when checking if a message is translateable.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-05-30T04:18:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-05-30T04:18:33.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/40899",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=keilnoth",
                        "name": "keilnoth",
                        "displayName": "Eric Jeker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "For me, Zend_Validate_Abstract is buggy as well simply because if the getMessages() method is used, like it's done in Zend_Form_Element (line 1368, v1.10), the _createMessage() method in Zend_Validate_Abstract is used to generate the error messages, and in that method, the problem is exactly the same than specified above.\r\n\r\nSee the code below of the _createMessage() method:\r\n\r\n{code} \r\nif (null !== ($translator = $this->getTranslator())) {\r\n    if ($translator->isTranslated($message)) {\r\n        $message = $translator->translate($message);\r\n    } elseif ($translator->isTranslated($messageKey)) {\r\n        $message = $translator->translate($messageKey);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n{code} \r\n\r\nThe message is not logged because isTranslated() is used.\r\n\r\nTo re-create the problem, create a Form with a Zend_Form_Element_Text element, setRequired(true) and add a NotEmpty validator. Submit the form with nothing in the field.\r\n\r\nBe aware that, if the element already has error messages, then everything work fine because _getErrorMessages() of Zend_Form_Element is used and isTranslated() in not used in that one.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=keilnoth",
                        "name": "keilnoth",
                        "displayName": "Eric Jeker",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-06-07T09:22:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-06-07T09:22:33.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
    },
